Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA fluttering cave bat squeaks angrily here.``
Girl on guard duty
`cA robust woman sits crosslegged under a tree, using her knife to smoothen the shaft of an arrow.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis robust woman has had years of experience of making bows and arrowsfor the village of the amazons.  She looks up and smiles as you approachher.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cA butcher cleaves big chunks of meat with single chops.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis female is dressed in a leather apron and wielding a butcher'scleaver.  She looks you up and down as if to decide whether youd taste good.``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cA group of amazon women dances around the totem pole, moving in rhythm to the drums.``
Mobiles.Description: `dWearing only leather loin cloths, this group of amazons dance aroundhere, lost of the rhythm of the music.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cAn old woman wearing a drab green dress sits on the only chair in the room.``
`cThe tanner sweats as she prepares a skin here.``
`cDarra, the blacksmith, stands behind the counter polishing a silver dagger.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis is Darra, the blacksmith, and she is almost obscenely muscled forbeing a woman.  Her arms sport burn scars from the furnaces and the otherduties she performs as a blacksmith.  ``

Mobiles.ShortDescription: A practice dummy made of grass
Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA practice dummy made of grass swings back and forth on a rope attached to an old fig tree.``
Mobiles.Description: `cA man-sized dummy made of a wooden frame with grass bound around it.It swings in the wind, a poor imitation of a fighting opponent, but at leastone can practice swinging at a moving target.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cAn amazon warrior has been called by the alarm.
`cA group of amazon elders sits around a fire, arguing.``
Mobiles.Description: `dA group of older amazon women sit squabbling among themselves aboutmatters that no one but themselves may know.  They quiet down as you drawcloser, and you notice a readiness in their eyes.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aThis monstrosity was once an amazon woman, now her flesh is rotting around her.``
Mobiles.Description: `hOnce a beautiful amazon warrior, this woman has been cursed in someinexplicable way that is slowly turning her into one of the undead.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cA girl is behind the stand, selling her fruits and vegetables.``
Mobiles.Description: `dA dimple-faced girl smiles up at you, offering you a view of hermouth-watering goods.  She tells you how cheap her wares are, and adds thatshe would do anything to satisfy her costumers.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cAn amazonian girl has been left in charge with guard duty here.``
Mobiles.Description: `dA lean teenage girl keeps watch over the plains below, watching out forapproaching enemies.  She is painted with the traditional red and yellowsymbols of the amazons, wearing only a leather loincloth and a brown grassshirt.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cAn old woman sits here, peering up at you.``
Mobiles.Description: `dWhat is this old woman doing out here in the wilderness?  She issitting with her back to the solid mountain, knitting a scarf that you havea hard time understanding the use for in this warm climate.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aVines flail at you, whipping the life from you, just so you can be the dinner of this carnivorous plant!``
Mobiles.Description: `cPast the snapping jaws of this blood-red flower you see a bloatedstomach filled with acid, to digest the victims it manages to drag into itslair.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA mass of legs clatters against the ground as this giant insect attacks!``
Mobiles.Description: `bSnapping pincers wants to devour you alive, preferably with as muchscreaming involved as possible!  Behold the reward of greediness.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cAn amazon sits on a branch, studying the ground, looking for animals.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis amazon is painted with red, yellow and green colored, making herappearance quite fierce.  She is wielding three colored spears, typical tothe amazon tribeswomen.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA fanged skull monkey swings from branch to branch.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThe skull monkey got its name from its prized midnight-black fur andthe white facial hair, making it look like a floating skull in the darkforest.  And many a wounded adventurer can bear testament to its the temperthat matches the skull monkey's visage.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `aA six-legged lizard slithers through the underbrush.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis is the red-tailed flint lizard, and why it was named after its redtail instead of the six legs, nobody will ever know.  The lizard is said tobe more stubborn and aggressive than a wolverine with cubs.  Combine thatwith its fire-breath and you have got a quite formidable opponent.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA striped lion stalks its prey, almost invisible in the tall grass.``
Mobiles.Description: `dRed and grey stripes on the sides of this lion makes it hard to detectin the rust-colored grass of the grasslands.  No animal in the grasslands isfeared more.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `dA magnificent ostrich keeps watch for predators here, occasionally pecking at the ground.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis big bird cocks its head at you with an attitude that only ablue-feathered ostrich could muster.  It looks you up and down with itssaucer eyes, then dismisses you, flicking its blue tail-feathers at youdefiantly.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cAn amazon is hiding behind a tree, watchign a cleverely hidden trap intently.``
Mobiles.Description: `dClad in painted leather breeches and tunic, this amazon trapper blendsinto the surrounding forest.  With a small string in her hand she waits foran insuspecting animal to walk into her trap.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `oA crab scuttles up to you, snaps its claws in challenge, then runs away.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis is the crab of false bravado.  It is known for challengingintruders of its territory by snapping its claws at them, and then runningaway, hiding under a rock.  ``

Mobiles.LongDescription: `cAn amazon hunting party is following the tracks of a lion here.``
Mobiles.Description: `dThis hunting party moves silently through the grasslands, tracking somelarge animal.  Each of the women in the group has either a shortbow or awooden spear wielded.  ``

Rooms.RoomDescription: `aEver-rolling waves lick the black sand of this desolate shore and whiteseashells glints like eyeballs among the sharp rocks that jut out of theflattened dunes of sand as if defending against any ships that would steertoo close.  ``
`dThe hull of the shipwreck, sporting holes and cracks, provides a meagerprotection against the sun and wind.  Although there is little else toprovide that kind of protection on this beach.  ``

`dThe wind brings the sweet smell of rot from the north, bending thegrass of this great grassland.  To the east there is a great mountain, andthere seem to be some kind of large wooden structure halfway up the rockface.  To the far south a humid rainforest blocks the view of the ocean.  ``

Rooms.RoomName: At the Base of the Mountain
Rooms.RoomDescription: `dFlowers adorn the otherwise cold rock of the mountain here, cared forby an old woman that hobbles around here.  Far above, on the mountain side,one can spot a few wooden structures, what could that be?  ``
`cBefore you lies the mountain village of the amazons.  A small societythat consists solely of women.  Women eye you varily as you arrive, thiscould mean trouble...  ``
`mamazon warriors glaring?
`cThis is where the villagers come to get their water, its the well.  Adaily meeting place for all the women in the village.  Buckets sit next tothe square well, each attached to a rope.  ``
`cClouds of flies buzz around the skinned animal carcasses outside thebutchery to the east - a small wooden structure that seem to hang off thevery cliffside of the mountain.  ``

`cThe smell of this room is a mix of food and raw meat, the butcher chopsbig chunks of meat with one hand and handling a frying pan with the other.The rickety walls of this single-room house are black from soot and youreally dont feel like staying too long.  ``

Rooms.RoomName: `bA Copse by the Edge of the Cliff``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `cA few thick-leafed threes stand here, protecting against the unmercifulglare of the sun.  Several hammocks in earthy colors hang between thetrunks, some occupied by amazon women.  ``

`cFrom between the dangling cages you can see the vast expanses of thegrasslands, and north of that, the rotten lands.  The cursed swamps, killingall living things within its grasp, seem to slowly crawl towards the coast.
`cBags full of fruit and vegetables pile up against the sides of thestand, and barely visible behind it, a girl stands, smiling broadly at everypassing person.  ``

`cJudging from how well kept this place is, and the amount of incensesticks and wooden tablets, this must be a holy place to the amazon women.  Araised platform, on which the amazons have placed offerings to the gods, isbefore you.  ``
`cThree logs lies neatly around a fire, perfect for leaning back on ifyou were to be an older person.  A blazing fire radiates pleasant warmth,giving off the smell of burning spruce.  ``

`cHammocks, the prefered place for the amazons to sleep, hang from theceiling of the cave, above a neatly organized room.  There is a desk and achair, a few chests and colorful carpets on the floor.  But in the back ofthe cave there is a grate, from which a pathetic whimpering can be heard.
`aThis is basically a hole chiseled out of the very mountain.  Apparentlyit is made to keep its resident trapped and unable to get out.  ``
`cThe smoky interior of this small hut looks like a medicine shop, rowsupon rows of small vials sit on shelves all around you.  The incense burnsmakes a wave of calmness blanket over you.  ``

`cLeading from the south, the center of the village, to the west, thetanner's shop, there is a small dirt trail.  Beside the trail, small brushgrows and above a small outcropping of the mountain gives shade from thesun.  ``

`cTools lie in neat rows on tables next to wooden contraptions thatstretch the hides of various animals.  A barrel sits next to the entrance,containing scraps of, what looks like, dried meat.  Not knowing what thatreally is, you decide to leave it be.``
`cFurnaces radiate extreme heat and light, bathing the smithy in an eeriered glow, casting flickering shadows all around.  Various wooden-handledweapons hang on display on the walls.  ``

`cThis small garden is separated by the edge of the cliff by a mossystone wall, barely high enough to keep lemmings from throwing themselvesover to certain death.  Luckily there are no lemmings here, but a beautifulgarden - trees, flowers, and even a small fountain on a marble dais.  ``

`gLight shines in through the waterfall, panting the wet cavern wallswith white and blue veins.  The noise of the falling water echoes throughthis small pocket of stone, making it impossible to hear or speak.  ``
`cThis is where the amazon women place their offerings to the gods (orgoddesses).  Gold and silver treasures lie here together with the occasionalsacrificed goat.  ``
`bViolent rustling is all around, it sounds like something dangerous isclose by, a something that just discovered you in the middle of its lair!

`aNow you have done it, you are once again crawling through a narrowspace hunting for treasure.  You do not seem to remember what happened allthe other times you did something foolhardy like this.  ``
`aSo here you are, following the trail of gold coins like a naive child.Crawling on, you fail to notice the heavy breathing in the dark passageahead, also the red glowing eyes escape your notice.  ``

Rooms.TpMsg: `xGreat going newb, you fell into ANOTHER trap.``
Rooms.RoomDescription: `aYou did not see THIS coming!  You find yourself in a giant insectoid'slair, and you are not alone.  To your total surprise, the insect appearsbehind you, trapping you.  Don't you feel stupid?  ``

`bBranches and leaves surround you, as they should, you sitting in a treeand all.  This is the perfect ambush spot, with animals passing under thetree, one could easily put an arrow in the back of them.  ``
